<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>Poems</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: "Georgia", serif;
      background-color: #0d0d0d;
      color: #d6d6d6;
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: auto;
      padding: 60px 30px;
      line-height: 1.9;
    }

    h1 {
      text-align: center;
      font-weight: normal;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .tagline {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #888;
      margin-bottom: 80px;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    .poem {
      margin-bottom: 80px;
    }

    .title {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      color: #fff;
    }

    p {
      white-space: pre-line;
    }

    footer {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 120px;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #555;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>Poems</h1>
<div class="tagline">
Welcome.<br>
These are words that survived silence,<br>
fragments of thought that refuse to be forgotten.<br>
Step carefully, for each line is a shadow.<br>
Let the poems speak what the night keeps hidden.
</div>

<div class="poem">
  <div class="title">Untitled</div>
  <p>
I learned  
that silence is not empty—  

it is full  
of things that refused to stay.  
  </p>
</div>

<div class="poem">
  <div class="title">Whispers</div>
  <p>
Some nights,  
the air remembers what we forget.  

Voices linger  
between walls and worn-out dreams.  
  </p>
</div>

<div class="poem">
  <div class="title">Afterlight</div>
  <p>
When the world sleeps,  
I write the things it cannot see.  

Ink spills quietly,  
like shadows chasing the last of the sun.  
  </p>
</div>  </p>
</div>

<footer>
  © Emmanuel — all words kept intact.
</footer>

</body>
</html>
